CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1962, pg. 8, reads: "Career Consultants - A career conference, "Preparation Starts Today," was co-sponsored Tuesday at Herron Hill Junior High School with the Urban League of Pittsburgh. Among the consultants were (left to right): Wilson Allen, civil engineer, Allegheny County Health Department; Charles Steckle, supervisor, drafting and design, Edgar Thompson Works; Charles Cooper, community services specialist, Urban League; Philip Allen, management trainee, Kaufmann's; William Blake, ex-officio officer, International Association of Machinists; James McCoy, staff representative, United Steelworkers of America, and Frank Andrews, registrar, Penn Technical Institute."
TitMainTitle: Career conference participants, from left: Wilson Allen, Charles Seckle, Charles Cooper, Philip Allen, William Blake, James McCoy, and Frank Andrews, gathered in Herron Hill Junior High School
